Wednesday, 26 June
	12.00
	National Council of Provinces Chamber, Parliament
	
	Parliament, Tuesday 25 June 2019 – The National Council of Provinces will hold its first ordinary plenary sitting at 12.00 on Wednesday, 26 June.
	
	The sitting is scheduled to elect the Chairperson for Committees, the Chairperson for Oversight and Institutional Support and the National Council of Provinces’ Programming Whip.
	
	The sitting is also scheduled to adopt Rules of the National Council of Provinces.
	
	First meetings of the National Council of Provinces’ 11 Select Committees are scheduled to meet on Wednesday morning to elect their chairpersons.
	
	Photographers and media who do not have parliamentary media access permits and wish to cover the 12.00 plenary sitting of the National Council of Provinces should send their details by 11.00 on Wednesday, 26 June to: Details needed are: Full name, ID/passport number, name of media organisation, designation (photographer, writer), email address, phone number(s)
	
	Media wishing to broadcast the sitting from the parliamentary precinct should also provide: Make of vehicle(s) and registration number(s) and expected time of arrival and of departure
	
	ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENT OF THE REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA 
	Enquiries: Moloto Mothapo – 082 370 6930 The copy of an Act of Parliament signed by the President is the official version of that Act and is given to the Constitutional Court for safekeeping.Read more